<br>
dragons not up, camp it or go do something else for once?<br>
<br>
<br>
anyway...back to vulak <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ugenadin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Genadin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/02 1:31:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9838.topic&index=111>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sky??</span><hr size=1> I seriously doubt Vulak has gone anywhere.  We cleared all but 2 Ntov dragons tonight /hug empty lairs.  And if anyone noticed there use to be 6 untargetable drakes in Vulak's chamber.  At the end of the night there was 1 or 2 left.  I am pretty sure all you need to do is clear all 14 other dragons and Vulak will pop.  This could suck because like someone said before you could clear 12 or 13 and be waiting on a spawn.  If it does not spawn and another guild comes in kills that lone dragon and gets Vulak that would surely be a big disappointment. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ul1nd4r4.showPublicProfile?language=EN>L1nd4r4</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/02 1:36:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9838.topic&index=112>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sky??</span><hr size=1> &quot;Granted, Vulak was easy....but I don't think this was the best answer. Is it right to let people scoop up loot from an easy boss for over a year and then screw over the other people who are just getting a shot at him?&quot;<br>
 <br>
  This is how Verant works.  They stop beads, manastones, longswords of etherial energery etc. from dropping.<br>
 <br>
  This just goes along with how they operate on repairing their own screwups.  Necro/sk spells stacking giving crazy ATK, emergency patch, damage shields giving crazy damage, emergency patch.  Anything that HELPS players they're more than willing to emergency patch, but a problem like a skill or spell getting broken or not working at all, forget it, they'll get around to something that unimportant in a patch or 3.<br>
 <br>
  This random spawn is @#%$, they SAY it's for timezones but thats obviously a lie or they're idiots.  Instead of making respawn a multiple of 24, make it a multiple of 24 and ADD EIGHT.  Or simply move the patch by 8 hours each time.  There, timezone problem fixed. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uevilmagus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Evilmagus</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/02 1:55:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9838.topic&index=113>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sky??</span><hr size=1> On fennin a guild cleared VP today so he's not there.  Not sure if greeny drake was up in Vulak lair, but Vulak wasn't that's for sure.  We haven't released the Sleeper yet.<br>
<br>
~Evil <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uneuromt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Neuro  MT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/02 1:56:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9838.topic&index=114>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sky??</span><hr size=1> For goodness sakes, Vulak is not in PoA.  He's either 1)Gone from the game, or 2)A triggered spawn inside TOV.  But he's not in PoA.  His character model does not exist in PoA, therefore he cannot be there.  Since they did not patch the artwork for PoA, it's safe to say he's not there. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubingespiritslammer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Binge Spiritslammer</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/02 2:06:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9838.topic&index=115>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sky??</span><hr size=1> Wether or not Vulak is gone or not, his loot is still in the game definately.<br>
<br>
Check your Rowyl's armplates, they're suddenly CLR and SHM usable now.  They wouldnt retro fit a no drop item like that :)<br>
<br>
Hey, its something new.  As long as it isnt Tedious, its fine.  <br>
<br>
The flurry drakes so far are definate adds, no way around em.  Gotta fight aary + 2 flurries.  Of course i could be wrong, i'm just a cleric :)<br>
<br>
Binge<br>
High Priest of Brell<br>
Enshadowed - Brell Serilis <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukarak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Karak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/02 2:09:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9838.topic&index=116>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sky??</span><hr size=1> Well, as for sky, that depends. His current model surely isn't in PoA, unless they've been planning this for months and snuck an update for that in a previous patch, but there's nothing to say they can't chose to use a different model.  They've changed Kerafym's a time or two, and I think a few others, so it's not unheard of.<br>
<br>
Can anyone confirm or deny the presense of A_Generic_Dragon_Model in the PoA zone file?<br>
<br>
Just playing devil's advocate here, I too think he's probably just gone triggerable. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umertonthedorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Merton the Dorf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/02 2:13:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9838.topic&index=117>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Blah</span><hr size=1> Vulak or no vulak it's obvious now that you have to do a ring of fire like quest to get his loot. We've given it 3 or 4 tries now and during each one everything has despawned a minute or so into the 'quest'. Has anyone else had this problem?<br>
<br>
As for a randomized timer on everything...stupid. A guild can still hold a monopoly on north but now it just takes 2 or 3 hours longer and camping empty spawn points to do so. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utullaianstarchaser.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tullaian Starchaser</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/02 2:14:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9838.topic&index=118>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sky??</span><hr size=1> A semi-transparent dragon model was patched into the Sky zone about 4 months ago. At the time people said it was for some Sleeper reawkening quest. Perhaps its now for Vulak. Shrug. <br>
<br>
In any event E.Marr has the guardian guys and no Vulak ( sleeper dead on our server also ). Didn't try ToV today since so few things spawned so whacked other stuff. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uvenvensilentdagger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Venven Silentdagger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/02 2:23:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9838.topic&index=119>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sky??</span><hr size=1> They didn't patch PoA (zone files) so Vulak can't be there.<br>
NToV was way too easy before, why whine when they make it a bit more challenging?<br>
<br>
I find this to be very interesting, as long Verant didn't broke some spawns and scripts when adding this. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uravenwingedangel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ravenwinged Angel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/02 2:40:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9838.topic&index=120>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sky??</span><hr size=1> Personally, I think it's good that they randomized the spawn times on the mobs.  But I think in a place like NToV all the named should be on the SAME random timer, I.E. when one spawns they ALL spawns.  Cause clearing them all is supposed to be the point.<br>
<br>
I also think it's cool the way they attatch mobs to other mobs as like &quot;pets&quot;.  I think the whole game should have been this way.  I mean, mobs formed into groups.  Single pulling should not be possible without Harmonizing because mobs should be able to communicate.<br>
<br>
&quot;Hey Bob, some monk just chucked a ninja star at me, I think I'll chase him down the hall, wanna come with?&quot;<br>
<br>
Thats just my opinion, I think the whole concept of single pulling a mob by coming from exactly the right angle or whatever method you use is unrealistic and silly. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udalteneq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DaltenEQ</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/02 2:45:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9838.topic&index=121>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sky??</span><hr size=1> Aside a few minor adjustments, NToV is the same, its simply more dungeon crawling instead of pulling every dragon to the same 2/3 places in the entire north wing.  <br>
<br>
The flavor this patch added to NToV is what the game needed at this point.   <br>
<br>
The highlight of the evening was moving to Feshlak's lair and having feshlak spawn right on top of the guild before everyone was even in there, winning that fight was pretty damn fun.<br>
<br>
Vyemm was a fun fight, killing these dragons in their lairs is actually a lot more fun then having them pulled to a wall where you can hide behind.  Who would have thought?<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukeadaiansongborne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Keadaian Songborne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/02 2:49:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9838.topic&index=122>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sky??</span><hr size=1> There is a dragon model in the global files... either that or there are models in most zones, since Nagafen was out of his lair and in some interesting places on Tribunal today... So don't rule sky out entirely.<br>
<br>
I think the more logical answer is that VI randomized spawn times on all ToV dragons and for once had enough foresight to realize the potential problem of vulak spawning before Vyemm and Zlexax.  I side with those that favor fire.... That is to say I suspect that either Vulak is in a ring of fire type event in his old lair or that he won't spawn until all of the other dragons have been killed.  Of course this means that the guild that kills the last dragon will get to Vulak even if another guild killed all of the other dragons.   Kinda sucks if the last dragon is say... Feshlak.<br>
<br>
In the mean time, they made all of ToV harder, which means that for at least a while, there will be boss mobs up for a few days after each patch.  Uber guilds will be busy because their kill rate will be slower, so &quot;lesser&quot; mobs that they might otherwise kill out of boredom will be left up for up and coming guilds to cut their teeth on.  <br>
<br>
